types.name: Int
types.description: The `Int` scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

types.name: String
types.description: The `String` scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.

types.name: Timeline
types.description: A timeline is a way of displaying a list of events in chronological order, sometimes described as a project artifact.

types.name: Drawing
types.description: Drawing is a form of visual art that makes use of any number of drawing instruments to mark a two-dimensional medium.

types.name: Person
types.description: A person is a human being (man, woman or child).

types.name: Poem
types.description: Poetry is a form of literature that uses aesthetic and rhythmic qualities of language—such as phonaesthetics, sound symbolism, and metre—to evoke meanings in addition to, or in place of, the prosaic ostensible meaning.

types.name: Poet
types.description: A poet is a person who writes poetry.

types.name: Picture
types.description: An image is an artifact that depicts or records visual perception, for example a two-dimensional picture, that has a similar appearance to some subject – usually a physical object or a person, thus providing a depiction of it.

types.name: Painter
types.description: Painting is the practice of applying paint, pigment, color or other medium to a surface.

types.name: Image
types.description: A container to store additional images

types.name: Painting
types.description: Painting is the practice of applying paint, pigment, color or other medium to a surface.

types.name: Inventor
types.description: In patent law, an inventor is the person, or persons in United States patent law, who contribute to the claims of a patentable invention.

types.name: Allegory
types.description: As a literary device, an allegory in its most general sense is an extended metaphor.

types.name: Photography
types.description: Photography is the science, art and practice of creating durable images by recording light or other electromagnetic radiation, either electronically by means of an image sensor, or chemically by means of a light-sensitive material such as photographic film.

types.name: ArtHistorian
types.description: The history of art is the history of any activity or product made by humans in a visual form for aesthetical or communicative purposes, expressing ideas, emotions or, in general, a worldview.

types.name: Politician
types.description: A politician, political leader, or political figure is a person who is involved in influencing public policy and decision making.

types.name: WarArtist
types.description: A war artist depicts some aspect of war through art. The art might be a pictorial record, or it might commemorate how war shapes lives. War artists explore the visual and sensory dimensions of war, often absent in written histories or other accounts of warfare.

types.name: Mosaic
types.description: Mosaic is the art of creating images with an assemblage of small pieces of colored glass, stone, or other materials.

types.name: StainedGlass
types.description: Figurative stained glass windows are assembled by fitting glass panes of different shapes and colours in a network of grooved strips of lead with an H-shaped cross-section.

types.name: Gallery
types.description: Gallery as commercial entity (as opposed to museum)

types.name: Photographer
types.description: Photography is the science, art and practice of creating durable images by recording light or other electromagnetic radiation, either electronically by means of an image sensor, or chemically by means of a light-sensitive material such as photographic film.

types.name: Number
types.description: A number is a mathematical object used to count, measure, and label.

types.name: Illustrator
types.description: An illustration is a visualization or a depiction made by an artist, such as a drawing, sketch, painting, photograph, or other kind of image of things seen, remembered or imagined, using a graphical representation.

types.name: ComputerGraphics
types.description: Computer graphics are pictures created using computers and the representation of image data by a computer specifically with help from specialized graphic hardware and software.

types.name: FilmMaker
types.description: Filmmaking is the process of making a film.

types.name: Linocut
types.description: Linocut is a printmaking technique, a variant of woodcut in which a sheet of linoleum is used for the relief surface.

types.name: BrandAmbassador
types.description: Brand ambassador is a marketing term for a person employed by an organization or company to promote its products or services within the activity known as branding.

types.name: Literature
types.description: Literature, in its broadest sense, is any written work; etymologically the term derives from Latin literatura/litteratura "writing formed with letters", although some definitions include spoken or sung texts.

types.name: Light
types.description: Light usually refers to visible light, which is electromagnetic radiation that is visible to the human eye and is responsible for the sense of sight.

types.name: Caricaturist
types.description: A caricature is a rendered image showing the features of its subject in a simplified or exaggerated way.

types.name: Composer
types.description: A composer is a person who creates music, either by musical notation or oral tradition, for interpretation and performance, or through direct arranging, recording and processing of sonic material.

types.name: Fresco
types.description: Fresco is a technique of mural painting executed upon freshly-laid, or wet lime plaster.

types.name: Theme
types.description: In contemporary literary studies, a theme is the central topic a text treats.

types.name: Pigment
types.description: A pigment is a material that changes the color of reflected or transmitted light as the result of wavelength-selective absorption.

types.name: Colour
types.description: Colour is the visual perceptual property corresponding in humans to the categories called red, blue, yellow, and others.

types.name: Intention
types.description: Intention is a mental state that represents a commitment to carrying out an action or actions in the future.

types.name: Petroglyph
types.description: Petroglyphs are pictogram and logogram images created by removing part of a rock surface by incising, picking, carving, and abrading.

types.name: Patron
types.description: Patronage is the support, encouragement, privilege, or financial aid that an organization or individual bestows to another.

types.name: Play
types.description: A play is a form of literature written by a playwright, usually consisting of scripted dialogue between characters, intended for theatrical performance rather than just reading.

types.name: Architect
types.description: An architect is a person who plans, designs, and oversees the construction of buildings.

types.name: Leader
types.description: Leadership has been described as "a process of social influence in which a person can enlist the aid and support of others in the accomplishment of a common task".

types.name: Matchbox
types.description: A matchbox is a box made of cardboard or thin wood designed to hold matches.

types.name: Naturalist
types.description: Natural history is the research and study of organisms including plants or animals in their environment, leaning more towards observational than experimental methods of study.

types.name: Sculpture
types.description: Sculpture is the branch of the visual arts that operates in three dimensions.

types.name: Advert
types.description: Advertising is a form of marketing communication used to persuade an audience to take or continue some action, usually with respect to a commercial offering, or political or ideological support.

types.name: Bust
types.description: A bust is a sculpted or cast representation of the upper part of the human figure, depicting a person's head and neck, as well as a variable portion of the chest and shoulders.

types.name: Anonymous
types.description: Anonymity, adjective "anonymous", is derived from the Greek word ἀνωνυμία, anonymia, meaning "without a name" or "namelessness".

types.name: Poetry
types.description: Poetry is a form of literature that uses aesthetic and rhythmic qualities of language—such as phonaesthetics, sound symbolism, and metre—to evoke meanings in addition to, or in place of, the prosaic ostensible meaning.

types.name: Pattern
types.description: A pattern, apart from the term's use to mean "Template", is a discernible regularity in the world or in a manmade design.

types.name: Music
types.description: Music is an art form whose medium is sound.

types.name: Print
types.description: Printmaking is the process of making artworks by printing, normally on paper.

types.name: Science
types.description: In the broadest sense, science (from the Latin "to know") refers to any systematic methodology which attempts to collect accurate information about reality and to model this in a way which can be used to make reliable, concrete and quantitative predictions about future events and observations.

types.name: Pornography
types.description: Pornography is the portrayal of sexual subject matter for the purpose of sexual arousal.

types.name: MagazineArticle
types.description: An article is a written work published in a print or electronic medium.

types.name: Geographer
types.description: A geographer is a scholar whose area of study is geography, the study of Earth's natural environment and human society.

types.name: BookCover
types.description: A book cover is any protective covering used to bind together the pages of a book.

types.name: Writer
types.description: A writer is a person who uses written words in various styles and techniques to communicate ideas.

types.name: Invention
types.description: An invention is a unique or novel device, method, composition or process.

types.name: Runestone
types.description: A runestone is typically a raised stone with a runic inscription, but the term can also be applied to inscriptions on boulders and on bedrock.

types.name: Topography
types.description: Topography is a field of geoscience and planetary science comprising the study of surface shape and features of the Earth and other observable astronomical objects including planets, moons, and asteroids.

types.name: Ceramics
types.description: In art history, ceramics and ceramic art mean art objects such as figures, tiles, and tableware made from clay and other raw materials by the process of pottery.

types.name: School
types.description: A school is an institution designed for the teaching of students under the direction of teachers.

types.name: Publisher
types.description: This type is used for any company or organization that has published a book.

types.name: Printmaker
types.description: Printmaking is the process of making artworks by printing, normally on paper.

types.name: Religion
types.description: A religion is an organized collection of beliefs, cultural systems, and world views that relate humanity to an order of existence.

types.name: Map
types.description: A map is a symbolic depiction highlighting relationships between elements of some space, such as objects, regions, and themes.

types.name: Mythology
types.description: Mythology can refer either to the collected myths of a group of people—their body of stories which they tell to explain nature, history, and customs—or to the study of such myths.

types.name: Photograph
types.description: A photograph or photo is an image created by light falling on a light-sensitive surface, usually photographic film or an electronic medium such as a CCD or a CMOS chip.

types.name: Mathematician
types.description: A mathematician is a person with an extensive knowledge of mathematics who uses this knowledge in their work, typically to solve mathematical problems.

types.name: Mood
types.description: A mood is an emotional state.

types.name: Temperature
types.description: A temperature is a comparative objective measure of hot and cold.

types.name: Film
types.description: A film, also called a movie or motion picture, is a series of still images which, when shown on a screen, creates the illusion of moving images due to the phi phenomenon.

types.name: Iconography
types.description: Iconography is the branch of art history which studies the identification, description, and the interpretation of the content of images: the subjects depicted, the particular compositions and details used to do so, and other elements that are distinct from artistic style.

types.name: Magazine
types.description: Magazines are publications, usually periodical publications, that are printed or published electronically.

types.name: Surgeon
types.description: In medicine, a surgeon is a specialist in surgery.

types.name: Tapestry
types.description: Tapestry is a form of textile art, traditionally woven on a vertical loom.

types.name: Leaf
types.description: A leaf is an organ of a vascular plant and is the principal lateral appendage of the stem.

types.name: Philosopher
types.description: A philosopher, in a broad sense, is someone who studies philosophy.

types.name: Artist
types.description: An artist is a person engaged in one or more of any of a broad spectrum of activities related to creating art, practicing the arts, and/or demonstrating an art.

types.name: Postcard
types.description: A postcard or post card is a rectangular piece of thick paper or thin cardboard intended for writing and mailing without an envelope.

types.name: Philosophy
types.description: Philosophy is the study of general and fundamental problems, such as those connected with reality, existence, knowledge, values, reason, mind, and language.

types.name: Book
types.description: A book is a set of written, printed, illustrated, or blank sheets, made of ink, paper, parchment, or other materials, usually fastened together to hinge at one side.

types.name: PlasticArts
types.description: Plastic arts are art forms which involve physical manipulation of a plastic medium by moulding or modeling such as sculpture or ceramics, often in three dimensions.

types.name: Sculptor
types.description: Sculpture is the branch of the visual arts that operates in three dimensions.

types.name: Graffiti
types.description: Graffiti is writing or drawings that have been scribbled, scratched, or sprayed illicitly on a wall or other surface, often in a public place.

types.name: Illustration
types.description: An illustration is a visualization or a depiction made by an artist, such as a drawing, sketch, painting, photograph, or other kind of image of things seen, remembered or imagined, using a graphical representation.

types.name: GraphicNovel
types.description: A graphic novel is a book made up of comics content.

types.name: Calligraphy
types.description: Calligraphy is a visual art related to writing.

types.name: Provenance
types.description: Provenance, is the chronology of the ownership, custody or location of a historical object.

types.name: Explorer
types.description: Exploration is the act of searching for the purpose of discovery of information or resources.

types.name: Woodcut
types.description: Woodcut—occasionally known as xylography—is a relief printing artistic technique in printmaking in which an image is carved into the surface of a block of wood, with the printing parts remaining level with the surface while the non-printing parts are removed, typically with gouges.

types.name: Collection
types.description:
The entity that has ownership/rights over a set of artworks. Often also a museum.
A museum is distinguished by a collection of often unique objects that forms the core of its activities for exhibitions, education, research, etc.

types.name: Composition
types.description: In the visual arts—in particular painting, graphic design, photography, and sculpture—composition is the placement or arrangement of visual elements or ingredients in a work of art, as distinct from the subject of a work.

types.name: Ceramicist
types.description: In art history, ceramics and ceramic art mean art objects such as figures, tiles, and tableware made from clay and other raw materials by the process of pottery.

types.name: Architecture
types.description: Architecture is both the process and the product of planning, designing, and constructing buildings and other physical structures.

types.name: Year
types.description: A year is the orbital period of the Earth moving in its orbit around the Sun.

types.name: Graphics
types.description: Graphics are visual images or designs on some surface, such as a wall, canvas, screen, paper, or stone to inform, illustrate, or entertain.

types.name: Caricature
types.description: A caricature is a rendered image showing the features of its subject in a simplified or exaggerated way.

types.name: Teacher
types.description: A teacher is a person who provides education for students.

types.name: Shape
types.description: A shape is the form of an object or its external boundary, outline, or external surface, as opposed to other properties such as color, texture, material composition.

types.name: DeathMask
types.description: A death mask is a wax or plaster cast made of a person’s face following death.

types.name: OilPainting
types.description: Oil painting is the process of painting with pigments that are bound with a medium of drying oil.

types.name: Comic
types.description: A comic strip is a sequence of drawings arranged in interrelated panels to display brief humor or form a narrative, often serialized, with text in balloons and captions.

types.name: __Schema
types.description: A GraphQL Schema defines the capabilities of a GraphQL server. It exposes all available types and directives on the server, as well as the entry points for query, mutation, and subscription operations.

fields.name: types
fields.description: A list of all types supported by this server.

fields.name: queryType
fields.description: The type that query operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: mutationType
fields.description: If this server supports mutation, the type that mutation operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: subscriptionType
fields.description: If this server support subscription, the type that subscription operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: directives
fields.description: A list of all directives supported by this server.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name and description, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given `__Type` is.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an object. `fields` and `interfaces` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields` and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: LIST
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: NON_NULL
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

types.name: Boolean
types.description: The `Boolean` scalar type represents `true` or `false`.

types.name: __Field
types.description: Object and Interface types are described by a list of Fields, each of which has a name, potentially a list of arguments, and a return type.

types.name: __InputValue
types.description: Arguments provided to Fields or Directives and the input fields of an InputObject are represented as Input Values which describe their type and optionally a default value.

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: A GraphQL-formatted string representing the default value for this input value.

types.name: __EnumValue
types.description: One possible value for a given Enum. Enum values are unique values, not a placeholder for a string or numeric value. However an Enum value is returned in a JSON response as a string.

types.name: __Directive
types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL’s execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.

directives.name: include
directives.description: Directs the executor to include this field or fragment only when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: skip
directives.description: Directs the executor to skip this field or fragment when the `if` argument is true.
